10.4 Managing Packages with Yum

yum was created to be intuitive
	yum search - search for software in repo
	yum install - install software
	yum remove - remove software
	yum update - update all software installed. you can also run updates on single packages
	yum provides - searches deeper then the name and package, it can also search the files in the package. For example, yum provides */sepolicy
	yum info - request information about a package, shows detailed information on different packages, version, description, etc
	yum list - get info about different packages. Yum list can show you packages available and installed packages. yum list all will show you all packages in repo and yum list installed will show you all isntalled